begin_memory_text: We introduced ourselves, and we spoke about the study. I showed them my guinea pig and we spoke briefly about our pets.
middle_memory_text: We spoke about our desired careers and struggles. We bonded over similar tragedies and areas of concentration.
end_memory_text: We continued talking about our struggles and the way life has effected us and about how we feel distant from our families.
rest_of_day_open: I see my week to be very productive with applying to college, financial aid, and finding ways to make money. I see myself giving myself space from family and seeking more online friends. I also have been meaning to make more friends who are older than me and this was a great kickstarter to begin searching.
critical_positive: We had many similarities from our trauma, our stance on relationships to our area of concentration, and related career choice. I felt comfortable speaking openly about why I haven't gotten a bachelor of science degree and about something that has weighed on my shoulders. It may have been forced on my part (to talk about my trauma) but I cherish that I had the opportunity to talk to someone who can actually relate to me.
critical_negative: there was a point where my family called for me and I had created an awkward situation. There were times when I asked some questions but either they had previously mentioned the answer or they did not understand my question and provided an entirely different answer calling for a new conversation.

begin_memory_text: Asking about job, age, education what she wanted to do. We talked about our pets and pets in the past and what our pets do and what we feed them and how much fun they are and about pets we had in the past and what we think about them such as ferrets.
middle_memory_text: Medical  and what we have similar likes of the body and how it heals itself and the fascination with medical field and how I have a background in biology and nursing and similar things with school and how we had a bad background in childhood.
end_memory_text: How we both have gone through incest and have mental challenges due to that and how we are to get through life living with these challenges and having kids or not and if there are stigmas attached to these feelings and how mental "hugs" can help you get through some of these challenges. Actually stated she felt she was in a therapy chair!
rest_of_day_open: It was a good reminder of how important communication is and how maybe I should put myself out there more often to offer up myself to help other people who may be going through similar things that I am going through whether it is mental health or physical challenges or even things that other people may be going through with not having kids and how that other people can make them feel when it was not necessarily our choice. It's just what happened. I think this was a very positive experience and will affect me for some time.
critical_positive: That for our age differences we had a lot in common and seemed to be able to understand each other without having known each other, yet we are all in this great big vulnerable world and we need one another to pull the others along and make the world a better place. I felt this conversation was destiny.
critical_negative: It was just in the beginning finding out about each other and how to manuver without stepping on each other and worried me a little when her mom was calling for and wondering if one something was wrong or how that might interfere with our interaction and if it would take away our concentration and if I might say more than I should. I wanted to be respectful and not overpowering.
